query

Description copied from interface: Queryable
Answers a spatiotemporal query and determines what objects are no longer in the spatiotemporal region (removed)and what objects are new members of the region (added).

By convention, the components of each Vector3d encode the physical location in the following way:

  • x is degrees latitude.
  • y is degrees longitude.
  • z is elevation in meters relative to sealevel. (For example, 0 is sealevel, -1 is 1 meter below sealevel, 1 is 1 meter above sealevel.)

      Specified by:
      query in interface Queryable
      Parameters:
      llCurrent - spatial lower left corner of the search region
      widthCurrent - spatial width of the search region
      lbTimeCurrent - lower bound on time of the search region
      ubTimeCurrent - upper bound on time of the search region
      previousResults - the Set returned by the previous call to query
      fieldNames - the keys of each QueryResultHandle
      added - the QueryResultHandles of things that are new to the search region.
      removed - the QueryResultHandles of things that are no longer in the search region.
      context - a Map in which the implementation keeps per-client state. The caller must create the Map and must not change it.
      Returns:
      a Set of QueryResultHandle
